5 years with the love of my life 🤍 I’m so thankful I’ve had you by my side through the ups and downs these last 5 years - career changes, moving to a new city, losing family, gaining family, becoming parents. We’ve experienced massive grief and great joy together. We’ve held each other through pain and celebration. Whether we’re laughing or crying there’s no one else I’d rather spend every moment with for the rest of my life. It’s unreal that 3 months have already come and gone 🥲 Thank you for choosing us, Noelle. You are the sweetest, most beautiful girl inside and out! Being your parents is our greatest joy 💕
The first Noelle 🎄

2023, you have been my favorite of them all ✨ I’ve never been one to have a “word” of the year, but at the start of this year I felt the Holy Spirit impress the word “surrender” on my heart. 

Through every season this year, I’ve tried to lean into surrendering control and anxiety. Surrendering getting pregnant when I wasn’t sure what God’s timing looked like for me. 

Surrendering fear throughout the first trimester and beyond as I didn’t know what the health of me and my baby would hold in the future. Surrendering finances and career in an increasingly stressful economy. Surrendering my labor and delivery not going anyway I hoped it would.  Surrendering my recovery from a c-section and the frustration of not being able to physically do much of anything. Surrendering my body image as I discovered my new postpartum body. Surrendering my breastfeeding journey not looking like I thought it would. Surrendering the health and safety of Noelle as a new parent who is scared and learning every day. 

It hasn’t been easy and I certainly haven’t done it perfectly, but in surrendering to God’s plan for this year I have felt immense peace in situations that years prior would have sent me into a panicking spiral. At the end of the day, I know I’m not in control. 

This constant reminder to surrender to God’s plan has kept me at ease through a life changing year. I’m so thankful that God is good and that His plans are good. Here’s to 2024 and continuing to surrender to His plan for my life. I’m excited to see where He leads 🥂

Hard to believe 4 months has already come and gone 😭 We love you so much baby girl! You are our greatest joy 💕
